{"lemma":"صارِخٌ","slug":"صارِخٌ","root":"ص.ر.خ","root_slug":"ص-ر-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ر-خ","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24164"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AE%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"gaudy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"crude, coarse"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noisy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"flagrant"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"outrageous"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"shameless, shocking"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"egregious"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vociferous"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of صَرَخَ (ṣaraḵa, “to scream, to shout, to yell, to call”)."},"ipa":["/sˤaː.rix/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24164","headword_ar":"صَارِخٌ","root":"Srx","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Calling"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calling out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crying out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing so vehemently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"screaming;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SariyxN","text_ar":"صَرِيخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Calling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crying, for aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SariyxN","text_ar":"صَرِيخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaSorixN","text_ar":"مُسْتَصْرِخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SariyxN","text_ar":"صَرِيخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, S, A, K,) or the latter [only] of these, (T, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSorixN","text_ar":"مُصْرِخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaArixapN","text_ar":"صَارِخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aiding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succouring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an aider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a succourer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, A, Msb, K:) Az says that he had not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaArixN","text_ar":"صَارِخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense on the authority of any except As; but that all men agree that it has the second of the senses given above, and that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSorixN","text_ar":"مُصْرِخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the last of those senses. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amapN","text_ar":"اَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN Sariyxuhu","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ صَرِيخُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male slave"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose aider"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a female slave"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is a prov. applied in the case of a mean man who is aided by one meaner than he. (Meyd.) And it is said in the Kur [xiv. 27], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anaA bimuSorixikumo wamaA A^anotumo bimuSorixiY~a","text_ar":"مَا اَنَا بِمُصْرِخِكُمْ وَمَا اَنْتُمْ بِمُصْرِخِىَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am not your aiders, nor are ye my aiders."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aArixu","text_ar":"الصَّارِخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) because he cries much in the night: and it is said by some to be tropical. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaArixN","text_ar":"صَارِخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry, informing a man of an event on account of which his aid is invoked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"announcing to him a death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AHeyth","S","A","K","T","Msb","Lth","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}